        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 6 at 4:42PM EDT by NWS Wakefield VA</headline>
        <description>At 441 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Dillwyn, moving southeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down small trees and blow around
unsecured objects. Wind impacting handling of high profile
vehicles. Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

This strong thunderstorm will be near...
Guinea Mills around 500 PM EDT.

Other locations impacted by this storm include Raines Tavern, McRae,
Angola, Hawk, and Stoddert.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
